* Set the ANDROID_NDK_HOME environment variable to point to the folder
  containing the Android NDK.
* Edit build.gradle to suit your needs.
  You should -at least- edit applicationId and the signing keys stuff to match your system.
* Download gradle 2.14.1 (might work on later versions) bin package from
  http://services.gradle.org/distributions/gradle-2.14.1-bin.zip
* Unzip it to some folder ([GRADLE_FOLDER]).
* Open a command line prompt at this folder
* Run [GRADLE_FOLDER]/gradle wrapper
* If that succeeds, build the code with "./gradlew assembleDebug"
* You can build, sign & install on device with "./gradlew installDebug"